channel.title: CVE Feed for NEC Corporation -- Aterm WF1200CR and Aterm WG1200CR
channel.description: The latest CVEs for NEC Corporation -- Aterm WF1200CR and Aterm WG1200CR

item.title: CVE-2018-16194|2024-08-05T10:17:38.393Z -- nec%20corporation -- aterm%20wf1200cr%20and%20aterm%20wg1200cr
item.description: Aterm WF1200CR and Aterm WG1200CR (Aterm WF1200CR firmware Ver1.1.1 and earlier, Aterm WG1200CR firmware Ver1.0.1 and earlier) allows authenticated attackers to execute arbitrary OS commands via unspecified vectors.

item.title: CVE-2018-16195|2024-08-05T10:17:38.325Z -- nec%20corporation -- aterm%20wf1200cr%20and%20aterm%20wg1200cr
item.description: Aterm WF1200CR and Aterm WG1200CR (Aterm WF1200CR firmware Ver1.1.1 and earlier, Aterm WG1200CR firmware Ver1.0.1 and earlier) allows an attacker on the same network segment to execute arbitrary OS commands via SOAP interface of UPnP.

item.title: CVE-2018-16193|2024-08-05T10:17:38.355Z -- nec%20corporation -- aterm%20wf1200cr%20and%20aterm%20wg1200cr
item.description: Cross-site scripting vulnerability in Aterm WF1200CR and Aterm WG1200CR (Aterm WF1200CR firmware Ver1.1.1 and earlier, Aterm WG1200CR firmware Ver1.0.1 and earlier) allows authenticated attackers to inject arbitrary web script or HTML via unspecified vectors.

item.title: CVE-2018-16192|2024-08-05T10:17:38.386Z -- nec%20corporation -- aterm%20wf1200cr%20and%20aterm%20wg1200cr
item.description: Aterm WF1200CR and Aterm WG1200CR (Aterm WF1200CR firmware Ver1.1.1 and earlier, Aterm WG1200CR firmware Ver1.0.1 and earlier) allow an attacker on the same network segment to obtain information registered on the device via unspecified vectors.
